1
00:00:18,834 --> 00:00:20,269
You're here.

2
00:00:21,395 --> 00:00:23,079
Did you invite him, by any chance?

3
00:00:23,079 --> 00:00:25,073
What do you mean? Who?

4
00:00:28,371 --> 00:00:29,639
Cha Dong Woo!

5
00:00:29,639 --> 00:00:32,341
He just arrived at the airport.
He's coming to see Yoo Jin's concert.

6
00:00:33,079 --> 00:00:34,680
Yoo Jin's father?

7
00:00:34,680 --> 00:00:36,115
My goodness...

8
00:00:36,716 --> 00:00:37,704
It wasn't me.

9
00:00:37,704 --> 00:00:40,019
I know about your relationship,
why would I have invited him?

10
00:00:40,019 --> 00:00:42,788
I know
the chairwoman sent an invitation every time

11
00:00:42,788 --> 00:00:44,223
but this time?

12
00:00:44,746 --> 00:00:47,788
Nothing will happen.
He'll just watch the concert.

13
00:00:47,788 --> 00:00:51,163
Cha Dong Woo started
Yoo Jin's phobias of planes and water.

14
00:00:51,163 --> 00:00:52,662
That perfectionist!

15
00:00:52,662 --> 00:00:55,913
What do you think he did
to that kid with his meticulous character?

16
00:00:55,913 --> 00:00:57,366
What?

17
00:00:57,974 --> 00:01:01,377
I don't know how much it'll mess up Yoo Jin
when he meets Cha Dong Woo.

18
00:01:03,020 --> 00:01:05,982
This can't happen.
I have to go and stop him.

19
00:01:05,982 --> 00:01:09,052
- Sun Young!
- Don't say anything to Yoo Jin.

20
00:02:05,027 --> 00:02:07,080
Min Hee! Min Hee!

21
00:02:08,121 --> 00:02:09,823
It's really difficult.

22
00:02:09,823 --> 00:02:12,559
Once the duet rehearsal is over,
it's our turn.

23
00:02:12,559 --> 00:02:14,538
Check your instruments.

24
00:02:14,538 --> 00:02:17,297
Did everyone hear the bandmaster?
Check your instruments!

25
00:02:17,998 --> 00:02:21,288
Jeez, why don't you just wag your tail?

26
00:02:21,288 --> 00:02:24,237
You're happy
after getting your bandmaster title taken away?

27
00:02:24,810 --> 00:02:27,330
Oh, I'm going to watch the duet rehearsal.

28
00:02:27,330 --> 00:02:30,913
What?
You want to see Nae Il wearing her dress?

29
00:02:30,913 --> 00:02:32,214
It'll ruin your eyes, Mini Min Hee!

30
00:02:32,214 --> 00:02:35,205
She's really pretty. It's fitted well, too.

31
00:02:35,205 --> 00:02:37,888
She's still Nae Il even if she gets prettier.

32
00:02:39,555 --> 00:02:41,123
By the way, where is Yoon Hoo?

33
00:02:56,888 --> 00:02:59,388
Nae Il! Seol Nae Il!

34
00:02:59,413 --> 00:03:01,084
Nae Il, open the door!

35
00:03:01,084 --> 00:03:03,486
- Seol Nae Il.
- What happened?

36
00:03:03,486 --> 00:03:05,288
Sunbae.

37
00:03:05,288 --> 00:03:06,923
Seol Nae Il, are you in there?

38
00:03:08,324 --> 00:03:09,330
What's going on?

39
00:03:09,330 --> 00:03:11,246
She locked the door from inside.

40
00:03:11,246 --> 00:03:13,455
She told me to leave the room
so she could change into her dress.

41
00:03:13,455 --> 00:03:14,704
Did she fall and get hurt?

42
00:03:14,704 --> 00:03:15,998
That's not it.

43
00:03:16,699 --> 00:03:19,001
She says she's not going to do the rehearsal.

44
00:03:24,908 --> 00:03:26,330
Here is the key.

45
00:03:26,330 --> 00:03:28,211
Nae Il is causing trouble today.

46
00:03:29,455 --> 00:03:30,996
I don't want to.

47
00:03:30,996 --> 00:03:36,262
I don't need any good opportunities.

48
00:03:36,762 --> 00:03:39,865
So I'm going to practice really hard.

49
00:03:40,466 --> 00:03:43,954
I'm not going to put on a mask this time.
I'll dress nicely.

50
00:03:43,954 --> 00:03:46,238
I'm really going
to perform on stage this time.

51
00:03:49,375 --> 00:03:52,945
As long as I don't get nervous,
I can do well.

52
00:03:53,625 --> 00:03:54,993
Guys.

53
00:03:56,128 --> 00:03:57,562
Can you excuse us for a minute?

54
00:04:23,704 --> 00:04:25,372
You...

55
00:04:26,273 --> 00:04:30,377
were in an especially good mood
since this morning.

56
00:04:31,913 --> 00:04:34,316
Now I know why.

57
00:04:36,451 --> 00:04:38,954
Although we're not together,

58
00:04:39,579 --> 00:04:44,037
we'll be on the same stage on the same day

59
00:04:44,037 --> 00:04:46,186
for the first time.

60
00:04:48,955 --> 00:04:53,893
If it's still too early for you
to be on stage...

61
00:04:55,381 --> 00:04:58,183
and if it's too difficult for you
to play in front of people

62
00:05:00,633 --> 00:05:05,204
then it's okay for you to stay there today.

63
00:05:12,497 --> 00:05:15,564
Until you want to open the door,

64
00:05:15,564 --> 00:05:17,168
I will wait.

65
00:06:03,581 --> 00:06:06,317
What happens if I disappoint them?

66
00:06:07,531 --> 00:06:08,866
Who?

67
00:06:09,641 --> 00:06:13,711
The people who had hopes for me
and who liked me...

68
00:06:14,791 --> 00:06:18,502
If I can't play the piano well
and can't be the best,

69
00:06:18,502 --> 00:06:20,296
I'm afraid they'll hate me.

70
00:06:30,413 --> 00:06:31,981
There is no one like that here.

71
00:06:32,850 --> 00:06:36,353
No one will turn away from you
because of the piano.

72
00:06:36,787 --> 00:06:38,656
If you don't want to, you don't have to.

73
00:06:41,984 --> 00:06:44,019
I didn't know you were scared.

74
00:06:45,154 --> 00:06:46,922
You were so good at the Mambo performance.

75
00:06:47,760 --> 00:06:51,764
I guess it wasn't a piano performance.

76
00:06:51,764 --> 00:06:54,266
I thought I was fine now.

77
00:06:56,268 --> 00:06:58,121
I thought I'd be able to do it.

78
00:06:58,121 --> 00:06:59,972
Yes, I know.

79
00:07:01,707 --> 00:07:02,829
I know.

80
00:07:02,829 --> 00:07:04,876
Even if you can't do it, it's okay.

81
00:07:05,544 --> 00:07:07,345
Until you can do it,

82
00:07:08,469 --> 00:07:10,004
I will wait.

83
00:07:14,976 --> 00:07:16,844
I will wait for you.

84
00:07:37,977 --> 00:07:40,163
Why is the conductor here?

85
00:07:40,163 --> 00:07:42,314
After our rehearsal,
it's the orchestra's turn.

86
00:07:42,962 --> 00:07:46,164
There will be no duet rehearsal.

87
00:07:47,720 --> 00:07:50,255
- What do you mean?
- The duet performance is canceled.

88
00:07:50,762 --> 00:07:52,762
Seol Nae Il is not in any condition
to be on stage.

89
00:07:54,432 --> 00:07:57,034
I'll talk to the school.

90
00:07:57,943 --> 00:07:59,544
I have to do this.

91
00:08:05,497 --> 00:08:06,998
Didn't you hear me?

92
00:08:06,998 --> 00:08:08,399
- Seol Nae Il...
- Still!

93
00:08:11,102 --> 00:08:12,904
I have to do this.

94
00:08:16,207 --> 00:08:19,210
This is why I can't stand
the ones who only talk about manners.

95
00:08:21,153 --> 00:08:24,538
What's your deal?
I said it's not going to happen!

96
00:08:24,538 --> 00:08:26,387
Are you going to force her
to go on the stage?

97
00:08:28,780 --> 00:08:29,981
What if I am?

98
00:08:31,562 --> 00:08:36,133
I have to perform a duet with Nae Il today
no matter what happens.

99
00:08:47,985 --> 00:08:51,405
If you have to do it, convince her first.

100
00:08:51,413 --> 00:08:53,511
- If you act like this...
- Move.

101
00:08:55,493 --> 00:08:56,860
Lee Yoon Hoo.

102
00:08:58,302 --> 00:09:00,137
Your usual self is better than this at least.

103
00:09:01,011 --> 00:09:03,013
You're really weird right now.

104
00:09:04,489 --> 00:09:06,163
Is it weird for a performer to go on a stage?

105
00:09:06,163 --> 00:09:08,092
Ask her nicely like you usually do.

106
00:09:08,839 --> 00:09:10,591
We have a rehearsal soon.

107
00:09:10,595 --> 00:09:12,096
I have no time for that.

108
00:09:39,824 --> 00:09:43,194
You have a problem
with your left hand, right?

109
00:09:44,751 --> 00:09:47,153
- It's hard for you to play.
- Shut up.

110
00:09:50,341 --> 00:09:52,309
I can do it today.

111
00:10:03,144 --> 00:10:04,845
What about the doctors?

112
00:10:06,484 --> 00:10:08,119
Fracture? Ligament?

113
00:10:09,996 --> 00:10:12,499
Is it the nerve?
It's like that even with medication?

114
00:10:12,499 --> 00:10:14,200
Can you quit your nosy interest?

115
00:10:16,121 --> 00:10:19,497
You are in no condition to play, are you?

116
00:10:19,497 --> 00:10:21,026
I can do it!

117
00:10:22,746 --> 00:10:26,016
Your duet is canceled.

118
00:10:26,016 --> 00:10:28,205
You're going overboard.

119
00:10:28,205 --> 00:10:29,920
It won't get ruined with one performance.

120
00:10:29,920 --> 00:10:32,371
If you feel pain
even after taking a pain reliever,

121
00:10:32,371 --> 00:10:33,523
it's serious.

122
00:10:34,050 --> 00:10:37,052
I can't let this happen.
I'm going to report it to the school.

123
00:10:37,803 --> 00:10:39,621
None of your business!

124
00:10:39,621 --> 00:10:41,807
I'll perform today as planned.

125
00:10:41,807 --> 00:10:43,641
It took so much for me
to hang on until now!

126
00:11:28,855 --> 00:11:33,493
When did you start playing the piano?

127
00:11:36,988 --> 00:11:39,157
Probably as soon as you opened your eyes.

128
00:11:43,288 --> 00:11:44,989
Same for me.

129
00:11:47,459 --> 00:11:49,218
In my memory,

130
00:11:50,455 --> 00:11:52,744
I've always been with my cello.

131
00:11:58,009 --> 00:12:00,278
I heard I was made to play
since I was three.

132
00:12:03,008 --> 00:12:04,809
Then it's been 20 years.

133
00:12:06,642 --> 00:12:08,403
If I get surgery on the nerve,

134
00:12:09,228 --> 00:12:12,964
the probability of playing the cello again
is almost zero.

135
00:12:15,861 --> 00:12:17,429
Even if I do...

136
00:12:22,194 --> 00:12:25,076
how long would it take
for me to play like this again?

137
00:12:28,240 --> 00:12:29,979
Today's performance...

138
00:12:31,788 --> 00:12:34,176
is about sending off my 20 years friendship.

139
00:12:36,668 --> 00:12:40,872
It's a requiem
that I'm offering for that friend.

140
00:12:45,222 --> 00:12:48,038
All that babbling. You're talking too much.

141
00:12:48,038 --> 00:12:51,930
Hanging out with Seol Nae Ill,
I've also become nosy.

142
00:12:54,690 --> 00:12:56,124
Requiem?

143
00:12:57,469 --> 00:12:59,237
That means your hand is really in bad shape.

144
00:13:00,385 --> 00:13:04,089
No wonder you were saving your hand
during practice.

145
00:13:08,651 --> 00:13:13,038
I'd get treatment first
if I had time for babbling.

146
00:13:13,038 --> 00:13:14,913
I'd never do anything
to overwork my hand that's already in pain!

147
00:13:14,913 --> 00:13:16,388
Don't say whatever you want
just because it's not your problem!

148
00:13:16,388 --> 00:13:18,456
You think your injury is none of my business?

149
00:13:18,456 --> 00:13:21,163
Even the losers with no talent
know that their hands are important.

150
00:13:21,163 --> 00:13:23,552
They're afraid they'd hurt their hands
working in construction...

151
00:13:24,846 --> 00:13:28,049
But what? A requiem?

152
00:13:29,684 --> 00:13:32,787
You didn't get treatment to prepare for that?

153
00:13:33,638 --> 00:13:36,441
If I were you,
I'd never do something like that.

154
00:13:36,941 --> 00:13:39,344
I'd play again
even if I had to get new hands!

155
00:13:40,831 --> 00:13:42,233
Get new hands?

156
00:13:44,062 --> 00:13:46,464
Go back to when I was three and start over?

157
00:13:47,121 --> 00:13:49,288
If I really like it,

158
00:13:49,288 --> 00:13:53,127
I'd never give up
even if I had to learn with kids.

159
00:13:54,125 --> 00:13:55,993
You have no confidence
in starting over again.

160
00:13:58,299 --> 00:14:00,234
That's why you're running away.

161
00:14:22,987 --> 00:14:25,790
It'll be easier to run away.

162
00:14:32,412 --> 00:14:36,079
If you abandon me now,
it'll be harder for you.

163
00:14:36,079 --> 00:14:38,306
You'll have nowhere to run to.

164
00:14:40,046 --> 00:14:41,247
I know.

165
00:14:53,392 --> 00:14:54,459
I know.

166
00:14:56,296 --> 00:14:58,331
Even if you can't do it, it's okay.

167
00:14:59,933 --> 00:15:02,067
Until you can do it,

168
00:15:02,067 --> 00:15:03,470
I will wait.

169
00:15:06,823 --> 00:15:08,358
He said he'd wait.

170
00:15:08,950 --> 00:15:12,954
I can't live as you
and make him wait forever.

171
00:15:17,645 --> 00:15:19,614
Goodbye, Seol Nae Il.

172
00:15:26,467 --> 00:15:28,336
Goodbye, Seol Nae Il.

173
00:16:12,304 --> 00:16:15,246
Where have you been again?
Have you seen Yoon Hoo?

174
00:16:15,246 --> 00:16:17,621
Yes, he's outside.

175
00:16:17,621 --> 00:16:20,871
Nae Ill's getting ready for the rehearsal
and now Yoon Hoo went missing.

176
00:16:20,871 --> 00:16:22,954
By doing this,
all of our rehearsal will be delayed.

177
00:16:22,954 --> 00:16:25,913
Seol Nae Il is getting ready
for the rehearsal?

178
00:17:00,048 --> 00:17:01,515
Seol Nae Il.

179
00:17:09,654 --> 00:17:11,259
Are you okay?

180
00:17:11,259 --> 00:17:14,629
Sunbae, your hand.

181
00:17:21,121 --> 00:17:23,290
What? You're not okay?

182
00:17:28,743 --> 00:17:31,378
Your hands comfort me as always.

183
00:17:35,012 --> 00:17:36,814
I'm fine now.

184
00:17:47,233 --> 00:17:49,035
It's no big deal.

185
00:17:49,819 --> 00:17:51,954
Why was I so afraid?

186
00:17:56,397 --> 00:18:00,101
Sunbae, will you sit in the audience seat?

187
00:18:04,011 --> 00:18:07,281
The longer you delay the surgery,
the harder the recovery will be.

188
00:18:08,041 --> 00:18:11,645
It might be difficult
to carry on your daily routine.

189
00:18:12,166 --> 00:18:16,904
The performance you have to do,
is it worth giving up your hand?

190
00:18:45,416 --> 00:18:46,767
Sorry, I'm late.

191
00:18:49,236 --> 00:18:50,871
Did you wait for a long time?

192
00:18:51,672 --> 00:18:53,538
No.

193
00:18:53,538 --> 00:18:57,820
Yoon Hoo, let's start. I'm ready.

194
00:19:00,655 --> 00:19:04,996
And thank you for choosing this music.

195
00:19:04,996 --> 00:19:07,495
- What?
- Sicillienne.

196
00:19:08,182 --> 00:19:13,487
I put my own meaning to this music
when I played it.

197
00:19:15,296 --> 00:19:20,201
Our performance today is a beginning for me.

198
00:19:22,079 --> 00:19:22,996
Of what?

199
00:19:22,996 --> 00:19:25,662
Whatever it is. Whatever.

200
00:19:25,662 --> 00:19:27,885
I feel like I can do anything.

201
00:19:31,822 --> 00:19:33,324
I can do this!

202
00:20:25,349 --> 00:20:27,205
Today's performance...

203
00:20:27,205 --> 00:20:29,686
is about sending off my 20 years friendship.

204
00:20:36,402 --> 00:20:38,621
You think your injury is none of my business?

205
00:20:38,621 --> 00:20:40,371
If I really liked it,

206
00:20:40,371 --> 00:20:41,756
I'd never give up.

207
00:20:44,952 --> 00:20:47,154
You have no confidence
in starting over again.

208
00:20:48,081 --> 00:20:50,083
That's why you're running away.

209
00:21:12,647 --> 00:21:15,150
Yoon Hoo, what's wrong?

210
00:21:15,726 --> 00:21:17,227
Nae Il.

211
00:21:18,629 --> 00:21:21,732
Let's cancel our duet.

212
00:21:23,153 --> 00:21:25,413
I don't think I can do this performance.

213
00:21:25,413 --> 00:21:26,770
What?

214
00:21:27,912 --> 00:21:28,912
I'm sorry.

215
00:21:36,754 --> 00:21:38,656
I'm really selfish.

216
00:21:40,370 --> 00:21:41,946
I only thought about myself.

217
00:21:42,802 --> 00:21:45,338
You're trying to start a new beginning...

218
00:21:46,917 --> 00:21:49,019
but I made you play a requiem.

219
00:21:50,814 --> 00:21:54,659
To me, Sicillienne is Faure's music.

220
00:21:55,606 --> 00:21:57,788
Faure's artistic talent

221
00:21:57,788 --> 00:22:00,711
that expressed his father's death
as requiem music.

222
00:22:01,939 --> 00:22:04,274
That was my last passion
that I was going to burn off.

223
00:22:05,182 --> 00:22:07,818
So when you chose this music...

224
00:22:11,038 --> 00:22:14,241
I thought of it
as the last music for my cello.

225
00:22:15,319 --> 00:22:19,890
But I didn't think
that it would be a beginning for you.

226
00:22:22,332 --> 00:22:23,633
I'm sorry.

227
00:22:38,524 --> 00:22:40,326
It's okay, Yoon Hoo.

228
00:23:04,008 --> 00:23:08,413
Yoon Hoo, this is not a requiem.

229
00:23:08,413 --> 00:23:10,782
It is Nae Il's Sicillienne.

230
00:23:11,742 --> 00:23:14,178
It's music for a new beginning.

231
00:23:15,269 --> 00:23:16,837
Whatever that may be.

232
00:23:56,821 --> 00:23:58,655
Hi, brother.

233
00:23:59,703 --> 00:24:02,705
Yes, I'm asking a favor of you to perform.

234
00:24:04,028 --> 00:24:06,730
Fill in for me just for today.

235
00:24:08,598 --> 00:24:10,400
Yes, thank you.

236
00:24:11,288 --> 00:24:12,495
I'm sorry.

237
00:24:23,781 --> 00:24:28,274
Mom, I'm going to the hospital.

238
00:24:30,636 --> 00:24:32,905
I'm sorry that I've been stubborn.

239
00:24:45,817 --> 00:24:48,829
Yes, Yoo Jin. I just heard from Yoon Hoo.

240
00:24:48,829 --> 00:24:52,746
He said he'd introduce us to his friend,
but he's coming from a concert too.

241
00:24:52,746 --> 00:24:55,538
So I'm going to ask Professor Ahn
to pick him up right away.

242
00:24:55,538 --> 00:24:57,579
We only have four hours until the concert.

243
00:24:57,579 --> 00:25:01,168
I'll take care of my orchestra members,
so don't worry.

244
00:25:18,519 --> 00:25:21,155
Now, it's our rehearsal time!

245
00:25:26,482 --> 00:25:28,121
You know this one. For the rehearsal...

246
00:25:28,121 --> 00:25:30,371
Do your best!

247
00:25:30,371 --> 00:25:34,035
- And for the concert...
- Perform with everything you got!

248
00:25:50,437 --> 00:25:53,740
Why are you in such good mood?
I've never seen you in such good mood.

249
00:25:55,689 --> 00:25:59,093
The duet of Seol Nae Il and Lee Yoon Hoo
is canceled.

250
00:25:59,932 --> 00:26:01,079
What happened?

251
00:26:01,079 --> 00:26:03,064
He got a little hurt
and went to the hospital.

252
00:26:03,464 --> 00:26:06,246
Tell them in a way
that it won't make them too surprised.

253
00:26:06,246 --> 00:26:08,538
Okay, don't worry.

254
00:26:08,538 --> 00:26:09,538
Thank you.

255
00:26:15,510 --> 00:26:17,111
Cha Yoo Jin.

256
00:26:17,111 --> 00:26:18,948
You know you're our conductor, right?

257
00:26:19,647 --> 00:26:23,417
You're smiling and looking confident,
so the members are energized, too.

258
00:26:33,801 --> 00:26:35,569
I guess nothing else will happen anymore.

259
00:26:36,831 --> 00:26:38,413
I heard Cha Yoo Jin is conducting.

260
00:26:38,413 --> 00:26:40,538
- Cha Yoo Jin?
- Yes. This has to be really good.

261
00:26:40,538 --> 00:26:42,970
It'll be awesome.

262
00:26:43,686 --> 00:26:44,921
Milch!

263
00:26:53,514 --> 00:26:55,916
Hello, Professor von Stresemann.

264
00:26:56,989 --> 00:26:58,993
It's nice to see you again,

265
00:26:58,996 --> 00:27:01,455
but when are you leaving this time?

266
00:27:01,455 --> 00:27:03,224
I'm not leaving.

267
00:27:04,058 --> 00:27:08,371
Where is Mi Na, the dean?

268
00:27:08,371 --> 00:27:12,491
I don't know.
I'd like to ask what this is all about.

269
00:27:13,049 --> 00:27:14,450
You do?

270
00:27:22,110 --> 00:27:23,811
Did my eyes go bad?

271
00:27:26,647 --> 00:27:28,782
Is that Cha Dong Woo over there?

272
00:27:29,565 --> 00:27:30,966
Pardon?

273
00:27:45,833 --> 00:27:48,205
You should just leave.

274
00:27:48,205 --> 00:27:49,413
There could be a problem

275
00:27:49,413 --> 00:27:52,455
if a player who canceled the performance
is sitting in the audience.

276
00:27:52,455 --> 00:27:55,265
I should see your concert.

277
00:27:55,800 --> 00:28:00,471
And I ran around to look for Yoon Hoo,

278
00:28:01,622 --> 00:28:03,023
but I couldn't find him.

279
00:28:03,996 --> 00:28:06,288
His treatment will go well, right?

280
00:28:06,288 --> 00:28:08,390
I'll check once this is over.

281
00:28:14,329 --> 00:28:16,413
Please come in.

282
00:28:16,413 --> 00:28:19,082
It's time. Let's...

283
00:28:29,913 --> 00:28:31,347
Hello?

284
00:28:32,215 --> 00:28:34,317
What's going on, Sunbae?

285
00:28:38,922 --> 00:28:41,424
This is very humble.

286
00:28:47,130 --> 00:28:48,621
Yes, Father.

287
00:28:48,621 --> 00:28:50,867
It has been a long time.

288
00:28:52,936 --> 00:28:55,579
When you're performing at a place like this,

289
00:28:55,579 --> 00:28:57,867
what's with your audacity
to send me an invitation?

290
00:28:58,611 --> 00:29:01,621
I didn't know
that an invitation was sent to you.

291
00:29:01,621 --> 00:29:03,621
I will make sure it never happens again.

292
00:29:03,621 --> 00:29:05,476
The order is wrong.

293
00:29:06,162 --> 00:29:07,579
First, you should say,

294
00:29:07,579 --> 00:29:10,800
"I'll never perform
at a place like this again."

295
00:29:12,126 --> 00:29:15,328
You're not saying
you still haven't gotten over it yet?

296
00:29:16,323 --> 00:29:19,913
For a man who should be studying abroad
and be on a global stage,

297
00:29:19,913 --> 00:29:22,962
you're wasting your time
in an orchestra like this?

298
00:29:24,390 --> 00:29:27,621
I'm learning and enjoying.

299
00:29:27,621 --> 00:29:28,538
It's not a waste of time.

300
00:29:28,538 --> 00:29:30,336
That is wasting time.

301
00:29:30,978 --> 00:29:36,050
And the result of that is this small room.

302
00:29:43,950 --> 00:29:47,386
You're still weak,
just the same as you used to.

303
00:29:48,246 --> 00:29:50,288
I should've ignored your mother's words

304
00:29:50,288 --> 00:29:53,251
and forced you into a hospital.

305
00:29:54,502 --> 00:29:58,514
Did you come to check on my condition?

306
00:30:03,923 --> 00:30:05,825
I stopped by on my way to Japan.

307
00:30:08,431 --> 00:30:12,145
It wouldn't be a concert
that I'd regret seeing, right?

308
00:30:12,145 --> 00:30:15,849
It's been a long time since I saw you,
but you're still the same.

309
00:30:15,849 --> 00:30:17,662
Of course.

310
00:30:17,662 --> 00:30:20,119
Because you still haven't made any progress.

311
00:30:39,163 --> 00:30:41,954
Did you see? Did you? Did you?

312
00:30:41,954 --> 00:30:44,330
There are cameras from TV stations
in the audience.

313
00:30:44,330 --> 00:30:47,071
As of today, we'll be a national orchestra!

314
00:30:50,558 --> 00:30:52,192
Please calm down.

315
00:30:54,192 --> 00:30:58,062
Have you heard from Yoon Hoo?
He's not answering my calls.

316
00:30:58,769 --> 00:31:03,173
I talked to Yujiin on the phone,
and it sounds like a ligament injury.

317
00:31:04,368 --> 00:31:06,991
Focus on us. We only have 10 minutes left.

318
00:31:06,991 --> 00:31:09,163
Finish up
checking your attire and instruments.

319
00:31:09,163 --> 00:31:10,995
- Okay.
- Okay.

320
00:31:15,871 --> 00:31:19,441
Cha Yoo Jin, you know
you're our conductor, right?

321
00:31:19,441 --> 00:31:23,538
Stay calm. You're the conductor.

322
00:31:23,538 --> 00:31:27,502
If you fall, your friends will fall, too.

323
00:31:28,012 --> 00:31:29,613
Friends?

324
00:31:30,692 --> 00:31:34,695
When you become the best,
friends will come along incidentally.

325
00:31:35,363 --> 00:31:38,566
Before that, everyone is your rival.

326
00:31:42,121 --> 00:31:44,123
Don't show your mind.

327
00:31:44,123 --> 00:31:48,026
If you do, that'll become your weakness.

328
00:32:30,241 --> 00:32:36,780
When I'm nervous,
holding your hand makes me feel better.

329
00:32:39,645 --> 00:32:41,704
That's how it's supposed to be.

330
00:32:41,704 --> 00:32:46,118
The body temperature puts people at ease.

331
00:32:56,934 --> 00:33:00,237
My hands are the comforting hands today.

332
00:34:01,746 --> 00:34:05,538
Rachmaninoff Piano Concerto No.2.

333
00:34:05,538 --> 00:34:13,413
This music was offered to the doctor
who cured his deep and heavy depression.

334
00:34:13,413 --> 00:34:16,954
A concerto that contains agony and healing.

335
00:34:16,954 --> 00:34:21,253
This music is talking to me now.

336
00:34:22,342 --> 00:34:26,078
"It's okay now. Everything will be fine."

337
00:34:32,538 --> 00:34:35,739
I have no reason to go
unless it's a top performance at a top stage.

338
00:34:35,739 --> 00:34:39,004
Make that happen if you want me to go.

339
00:34:40,204 --> 00:34:43,907
You're not saying
you still haven't gotten over it yet?

340
00:35:05,313 --> 00:35:07,314
Almighty Cha, it's okay.

341
00:35:07,800 --> 00:35:09,301
Just do what we did at the rehearsal.

342
00:35:09,735 --> 00:35:11,451
It's okay, Cha Yoo Jin!

343
00:36:39,031 --> 00:36:41,467
You were wrong.

344
00:36:42,079 --> 00:36:43,880
These are the friends

345
00:36:43,880 --> 00:36:46,850
who made me feel like I'm the best
even if I'm not the best.

346
00:36:47,999 --> 00:36:50,301
You were wrong again.

347
00:36:51,002 --> 00:36:53,913
The heart you've shown is not a weakness.

348
00:36:53,913 --> 00:36:55,756
It was returned with another heart.

349
00:38:20,258 --> 00:38:22,520
Yoo Jin, are you okay?

350
00:38:23,180 --> 00:38:24,996
You were really great today.

351
00:38:24,996 --> 00:38:26,662
- Awesome!
- Awesome!

352
00:38:26,662 --> 00:38:30,455
Yes, other conductors were
dropping and throwing their batons, too.

353
00:38:30,455 --> 00:38:31,538
He's right.

354
00:38:31,538 --> 00:38:33,881
It was special
that you never had that happen before.

355
00:38:34,478 --> 00:38:36,497
It happens all the time.

356
00:38:36,497 --> 00:38:40,921
It was easier to see
when you conducted with your bare hands.

357
00:38:40,921 --> 00:38:42,189
Me too.

358
00:38:47,688 --> 00:38:53,827
Min Hee, I'm sorry about the time I asked
if you wanted to bring sympathy.

359
00:38:55,460 --> 00:38:59,630
I didn't understand why you were hanging on
by working part-time jobs.

360
00:39:01,716 --> 00:39:05,886
Sunbae, it was a long time ago.

361
00:39:06,981 --> 00:39:11,218
Su Min, thank you for liking me.

362
00:39:13,060 --> 00:39:16,663
Thank you for not hating me.

363
00:39:18,313 --> 00:39:20,954
Hey, why are you making him cry?

364
00:39:20,954 --> 00:39:25,733
Il Lak, you're my best friend, too.

365
00:39:28,326 --> 00:39:29,961
Yoo Jin.

366
00:39:32,371 --> 00:39:35,174
Are you sick? What's going on?

367
00:39:35,792 --> 00:39:39,095
When people change suddenly,
I hear they'll die...

368
00:39:40,581 --> 00:39:42,497
Are you suffering from incurable illness?

369
00:39:42,497 --> 00:39:45,121
- Hey! How can you say that?
- Hey! How can you say that?

370
00:39:45,121 --> 00:39:47,845
I'm sorry. My mouth is the troublemaker.

371
00:39:49,557 --> 00:39:51,538
What's your illness?

372
00:39:51,538 --> 00:39:53,788
Are you really sick? Is it really tough?

373
00:39:53,788 --> 00:39:57,031
Is that the real reason you dropped it earlier?

374
00:39:57,031 --> 00:39:59,100
Because you're sick? Your hands are shaky?

375
00:39:59,100 --> 00:40:02,246
I told you something was off!
Does Nae Il know about this?

376
00:40:02,246 --> 00:40:04,038
It's not that...

377
00:40:04,038 --> 00:40:08,371
- Don't die!
- You can't die!

378
00:40:08,371 --> 00:40:10,377
Get away from me, you idiots!

379
00:40:12,999 --> 00:40:15,134
My true feelings are wasted on you.

380
00:40:16,249 --> 00:40:17,817
- Yoo Jin!
- Sunbae.

381
00:40:18,819 --> 00:40:22,623
- Yoo Jin is back to his normal self.
- That's Almighty Cha!

382
00:40:22,623 --> 00:40:24,625
What a relief.

383
00:40:40,565 --> 00:40:44,235
Now, I have to go on stage.

384
00:40:45,063 --> 00:40:48,621
I can't do anything
if I stay in the audience.

385
00:40:48,621 --> 00:40:50,284
Except for just watching.

386
00:40:53,867 --> 00:40:55,704
Dong Woo, wait.

387
00:40:55,704 --> 00:40:58,725
Cha Dong Woo, my ex-husband! Stop!

388
00:41:01,500 --> 00:41:04,579
Why didn't you pick up my calls?
I went to the airport to look for you.

389
00:41:04,579 --> 00:41:06,621
It's obvious
that you wouldn't say anything nice.

390
00:41:06,621 --> 00:41:08,456
I didn't want to fight.

391
00:41:09,124 --> 00:41:11,492
Cha Dong Woo didn't want to fight?

392
00:41:12,116 --> 00:41:13,194
You're getting old, too.

393
00:41:13,194 --> 00:41:16,413
If you don't want to fight again,
let's say goodbye here.

394
00:41:16,413 --> 00:41:18,032
Did you meet with Yoo Jin?

395
00:41:19,246 --> 00:41:21,648
I did. He's still the same.

396
00:41:23,718 --> 00:41:25,519
He can't go study abroad yet, can he?

397
00:41:27,108 --> 00:41:30,371
That's why we should've gone
with my way then.

398
00:41:30,371 --> 00:41:33,121
When you dragged a kid
who was about to pass out

399
00:41:33,121 --> 00:41:34,913
and put him on a plane?

400
00:41:34,913 --> 00:41:36,829
Don't you know
how it made things worse for Yujiin?

401
00:41:36,829 --> 00:41:39,246
You just left him alone
because he was crying and getting scared?

402
00:41:39,246 --> 00:41:41,522
We should've used shock treatment
if it was necessary.

403
00:41:43,776 --> 00:41:45,246
See?

404
00:41:45,246 --> 00:41:47,788
We're repeating the same conversation again.

405
00:41:47,788 --> 00:41:49,996
Call before you come from now on.

406
00:41:49,996 --> 00:41:53,098
You don't even know that it was you
who made Yoo Jin make a mistake today, do you?

407
00:41:53,554 --> 00:41:56,290
I do. He's still so weak.

408
00:41:59,507 --> 00:42:03,455
He was pretty calm
when he was handling the mistake.

409
00:42:03,455 --> 00:42:05,332
He has grown a bit.

410
00:42:07,101 --> 00:42:10,504
Tell him that I'll meet him
at a performance abroad next time.

411
00:42:22,581 --> 00:42:25,497
Let's talk a little today.

412
00:42:25,497 --> 00:42:27,288
We can talk about work tomorrow.

413
00:42:27,288 --> 00:42:30,305
You know it's not about work.

414
00:42:38,474 --> 00:42:41,377
Are you okay? Did you get hurt?

415
00:42:45,746 --> 00:42:47,163
Did you fall on purpose?

416
00:42:47,163 --> 00:42:49,205
I didn't.

417
00:42:49,205 --> 00:42:54,913
But now I see
that Mi Na is worried about me...

418
00:42:54,913 --> 00:42:58,213
I should've fallen more earlier.

419
00:43:03,732 --> 00:43:05,834
I'm still angry.

420
00:43:06,361 --> 00:43:10,398
I have no feelings
over someone who can leave anytime.

421
00:43:12,258 --> 00:43:16,829
This time, I really took care of everything.

422
00:43:17,972 --> 00:43:20,775
Because I don't have any more time.

423
00:43:22,398 --> 00:43:28,537
Mi Na, how much longer can we be together?

424
00:43:31,239 --> 00:43:33,829
You've thought about that kind of thing?

425
00:43:33,829 --> 00:43:38,497
I've wasted too much time
hesitating and misunderstanding.

426
00:43:38,497 --> 00:43:46,274
Now I don't want to live my life
wasting time anymore.

427
00:43:49,144 --> 00:43:50,946
What would you like to do?

428
00:43:50,946 --> 00:43:57,452
First, let's have a cup of coffee together.

429
00:44:01,456 --> 00:44:03,057
Miss.

430
00:44:08,014 --> 00:44:12,205
Watching you guys grow everyday
along with my son

431
00:44:12,205 --> 00:44:14,829
makes me deeply moved.

432
00:44:14,829 --> 00:44:18,371
That's why I prepared a big dinner for you.

433
00:44:18,371 --> 00:44:21,242
It's called 'a big dinner.'

434
00:44:23,979 --> 00:44:25,847
It looks great!

435
00:44:28,746 --> 00:44:30,748
My Mini Min Hee, eat a lot.

436
00:44:30,748 --> 00:44:34,163
Don't let this healthy woman take the food.

437
00:44:34,163 --> 00:44:37,121
- Yes, Father.
- Alright.

438
00:44:46,931 --> 00:44:50,829
Hey, it's weird.
Why do I feel like he hates me?

439
00:44:50,829 --> 00:44:53,738
- He does hate you.
- Very much.

440
00:44:54,485 --> 00:44:56,031
It's really good.

441
00:44:59,350 --> 00:45:02,319
Here, Shi Won, try this.

442
00:45:06,913 --> 00:45:08,662
What do you think? Is it good?

443
00:45:08,662 --> 00:45:09,916
It's good.

444
00:45:09,916 --> 00:45:12,919
Great. My father is a great cook.

445
00:45:52,960 --> 00:45:53,662
Fart Song.

446
00:45:53,662 --> 00:45:55,195
Yes?

447
00:45:55,929 --> 00:45:58,205
Hello, Professor.

448
00:45:58,205 --> 00:45:59,662
Hello.

449
00:45:59,662 --> 00:46:03,032
Your duet was canceled today. What happened?

450
00:46:03,871 --> 00:46:06,079
Yoon Hoo was really sick.

451
00:46:06,079 --> 00:46:07,336
He's sick?

452
00:46:08,184 --> 00:46:10,920
If it's bad enough
to give up a performance,

453
00:46:11,643 --> 00:46:13,189
is it his hand, by any chance?

454
00:46:13,895 --> 00:46:15,525
Yes.

455
00:46:16,192 --> 00:46:17,927
It must be serious.

456
00:46:19,859 --> 00:46:20,913
How did it happen?

457
00:46:20,913 --> 00:46:23,953
Professor, I plan to attend my lessons
starting next week.

458
00:46:24,461 --> 00:46:27,163
Okay, do that.

459
00:46:29,058 --> 00:46:31,330
What? You'll come to the lessons?

460
00:46:31,330 --> 00:46:33,129
Bye now.

461
00:46:34,884 --> 00:46:36,285
Fart... Fart Song...

462
00:46:41,210 --> 00:46:44,413
Professor Ahn? Yes, it's me.

463
00:46:44,413 --> 00:46:47,125
The student who plays the Fart Song...

464
00:46:47,829 --> 00:46:52,121
Does she have anything
that she doesn't like or she's scared of?

465
00:46:52,121 --> 00:46:53,431
Yes, yes.

466
00:46:54,436 --> 00:46:56,163
A fan?

467
00:46:56,163 --> 00:47:00,137
Why doesn't she like fans? Why?

468
00:47:05,992 --> 00:47:08,160
Yes, Yoon Hoo is sleeping.

469
00:47:11,029 --> 00:47:13,764
How did you know that my child had surgery?

470
00:47:14,231 --> 00:47:16,366
This is not an added number.

471
00:47:16,935 --> 00:47:18,623
Are you Yoon Hoo's friend?

472
00:47:18,623 --> 00:47:21,359
Never mind. I'm hanging up.

473
00:47:22,467 --> 00:47:24,902
What an annoying guy.

474
00:47:26,384 --> 00:47:28,330
Were you waiting for me?

475
00:47:28,330 --> 00:47:31,288
I wasn't. I was getting some fresh air.

476
00:47:31,288 --> 00:47:33,437
You were waiting for me.

477
00:47:35,563 --> 00:47:38,065
Should I check?

478
00:47:38,580 --> 00:47:39,621
Check what?

479
00:47:39,621 --> 00:47:41,045
Just wait.

480
00:47:43,876 --> 00:47:45,542
[Seol Rae Im]

481
00:47:48,114 --> 00:47:51,330
Seol Rae Im with three hearts!

482
00:47:51,330 --> 00:47:53,662
You put it in there, not me!

483
00:47:53,662 --> 00:47:56,704
You didn't delete it.
Doesn't it mean that you accepted it?

484
00:47:56,704 --> 00:47:58,639
There you go again, Nae Il.

485
00:48:03,508 --> 00:48:06,177
I got a call from Yoon Hoo..

486
00:48:07,053 --> 00:48:09,288
His surgery went well.

487
00:48:11,432 --> 00:48:12,800
I'm glad to hear that.

488
00:48:14,811 --> 00:48:18,047
Yes, me too.

489
00:48:18,648 --> 00:48:23,152
Yoon Hoo must have thought
it was his last performance.

490
00:48:24,362 --> 00:48:28,666
Still, a requiem was shocking.

491
00:48:36,165 --> 00:48:39,935
You'll also leave to study abroad soon,

492
00:48:40,548 --> 00:48:42,283
then I'll be left behind.

493
00:48:45,800 --> 00:48:47,067
Seol Nae Il!

494
00:48:53,427 --> 00:48:55,496
- You waited for us to come.
- No way.

495
00:48:55,496 --> 00:48:57,531
I know how you feel, my best friend.

496
00:48:57,531 --> 00:49:00,704
- What do you know?
- Almighty Cha, now I know how you feel.

497
00:49:00,704 --> 00:49:02,288
What do you know?

498
00:49:02,288 --> 00:49:05,704
Su Min, get away from him.
I look better next to him.

499
00:49:05,704 --> 00:49:08,807
Please get away from me, you idiots!

500
00:49:09,445 --> 00:49:12,038
Idiots, let's go to Yoo Jin's house
for the second round!

501
00:49:12,038 --> 00:49:13,392
- Let's go!
- Let's go!

502
00:49:13,392 --> 00:49:15,330
Hey, why are you going to my place?

503
00:49:15,330 --> 00:49:16,828
Is my place your second round?

504
00:49:23,248 --> 00:49:24,849
You're awake?

505
00:49:26,665 --> 00:49:27,932
Mom.

506
00:49:30,969 --> 00:49:32,270
Did you cry?

507
00:49:36,556 --> 00:49:38,913
I don't like to make women cry.

508
00:49:38,913 --> 00:49:41,686
Are you making jokes already? You seem fine.

509
00:49:44,423 --> 00:49:46,996
Your surgery went well.

510
00:49:46,996 --> 00:49:48,560
You don't need to worry.

511
00:49:49,320 --> 00:49:51,322
That's good.

512
00:49:52,617 --> 00:49:57,767
That means I won't have any problem
carrying on my daily life?

513
00:49:58,443 --> 00:49:59,910
Yes.

514
00:50:01,940 --> 00:50:06,036
Mom, I'm fine.

515
00:50:06,664 --> 00:50:12,146
Now I can really start over.

516
00:50:14,472 --> 00:50:17,108
I gained energy to start over.

517
00:50:47,547 --> 00:50:50,684
- Shi Won.
- Almighty Cha.

518
00:51:08,356 --> 00:51:10,497
Hello?

519
00:51:10,497 --> 00:51:12,538
Isn't this Cha Yoo Jin's cellphone?

520
00:51:12,538 --> 00:51:14,725
Sunbae?

521
00:51:16,325 --> 00:51:18,493
Oh, this is Sunbae's cellphone.

522
00:51:19,454 --> 00:51:22,624
Sunbae, wake up.

523
00:51:26,377 --> 00:51:27,811
Hey.

524
00:51:29,579 --> 00:51:32,163
Why did you sleep here
when your place is right next door?

525
00:51:32,163 --> 00:51:33,416
Leave now.

526
00:51:34,048 --> 00:51:38,038
But I'm really hungry.
Cook something for me.

527
00:51:38,038 --> 00:51:41,163
You're getting more brazen.
Wash first before you ask for something.

528
00:51:41,163 --> 00:51:44,127
Can I use your toothbrush?

529
00:51:45,059 --> 00:51:47,538
Even a husband and a wife
don't share a toothbrush.

530
00:51:47,538 --> 00:51:49,981
You're so narrow-minded.

531
00:51:49,981 --> 00:51:53,036
By the way, you have a call.

532
00:51:53,676 --> 00:51:55,244
Why are you telling me now?

533
00:52:01,411 --> 00:52:03,413
- Uncle.
- Yes, it's me.

534
00:52:03,926 --> 00:52:05,594
You're off from school today, right?

535
00:52:07,788 --> 00:52:10,079
Yes, it's the weekend.

536
00:52:10,079 --> 00:52:12,662
Then stop by at home with that girl.

537
00:52:12,662 --> 00:52:13,538
Who?

538
00:52:13,538 --> 00:52:15,963
The one who wants
to share a toothbrush with you.

539
00:52:18,661 --> 00:52:20,788
You have a lot of new things at your place.

540
00:52:20,788 --> 00:52:22,336
You're so well-prepared.

541
00:52:29,788 --> 00:52:31,624
Your uncle called?

542
00:52:31,624 --> 00:52:33,692
Did you do something wrong?

543
00:52:33,692 --> 00:52:35,371
No, not at all.

544
00:52:35,371 --> 00:52:38,079
When you've done something,
you deny strongly.

545
00:52:38,079 --> 00:52:39,288
What is it?

546
00:52:39,288 --> 00:52:41,133
I don't have any.

547
00:52:41,133 --> 00:52:44,038
How long do you plan to stay here?
What do you really have on your mind?

548
00:52:44,038 --> 00:52:47,306
Hey, I'm clear. I have nothing in mind.

549
00:52:47,306 --> 00:52:49,231
Boss, I'm here.

550
00:52:49,752 --> 00:52:51,121
You're here too, Yoo Jin.

551
00:52:51,121 --> 00:52:52,521
What are you doing here?

552
00:52:53,942 --> 00:52:57,413
Min Hee! She's your orchestra member.

553
00:52:57,413 --> 00:53:00,485
It's been a while
since I started working part-time here.

554
00:53:02,136 --> 00:53:04,851
Well, you're never really here.

555
00:53:04,857 --> 00:53:06,538
My son is like that.

556
00:53:06,538 --> 00:53:09,538
But what a strange coincidence, right?

557
00:53:09,538 --> 00:53:11,296
- Get ready.
- Yes.

558
00:53:13,022 --> 00:53:16,163
There's no mere coincidence, is there?

559
00:53:16,163 --> 00:53:19,121
- Hello, Boss.
- Hello.

560
00:53:19,121 --> 00:53:20,954
What brought you here?

561
00:53:20,954 --> 00:53:25,058
You didn't know?
I play the piano as a part-timer here.

562
00:53:25,759 --> 00:53:29,095
Please enjoy your mother-and-son conversation.

563
00:53:32,087 --> 00:53:34,038
Did you call her or did she come on her own?

564
00:53:34,038 --> 00:53:36,047
Who cares about who called first?

565
00:53:36,047 --> 00:53:38,717
I guess you made up with her, right?

566
00:53:38,717 --> 00:53:40,954
She's been really cold to me recently.

567
00:53:40,954 --> 00:53:42,704
But she's nice today.

568
00:53:42,704 --> 00:53:45,038
So you guys made up, right?

569
00:53:45,038 --> 00:53:46,820
I'm right, aren't I?

570
00:53:47,435 --> 00:53:48,837
Ms. Sun Young!

571
00:54:03,326 --> 00:54:05,027
Why are you surprised?

572
00:54:07,371 --> 00:54:08,772
Professor.

573
00:54:10,181 --> 00:54:14,952
Should I thank you
since you told me the name of the hospital?

574
00:54:15,807 --> 00:54:18,409
How could I lie to you?

575
00:54:19,217 --> 00:54:22,820
It's no big deal,
but thank you for coming by.

576
00:54:24,229 --> 00:54:26,097
"It's no big deal"?

577
00:54:27,038 --> 00:54:29,841
Can you play the cello again?

578
00:54:32,855 --> 00:54:38,560
Lee Yoon Hoo that I know
endures like an idiot.

579
00:54:40,571 --> 00:54:44,308
He wouldn't give up the stage
over a light injury.

580
00:54:44,749 --> 00:54:49,921
I'm not sure yet
if I can start playing the cello again.

581
00:54:51,082 --> 00:54:53,117
Please don't tell my friends.

582
00:54:55,962 --> 00:55:00,455
Different, but similar, too.

583
00:55:00,455 --> 00:55:03,037
- Pardon?
- You and Cha Yoo Jin.

584
00:55:04,158 --> 00:55:10,498
You're very similar
that you carry a problem alone like an idiot.

585
00:55:13,674 --> 00:55:15,576
What do you plan to do now?

586
00:55:16,083 --> 00:55:18,252
I'll live a different life.

587
00:55:19,120 --> 00:55:20,913
Since I'm starting over.

588
00:55:20,913 --> 00:55:21,855
Start what?

589
00:55:22,930 --> 00:55:24,364
Whatever it is.

590
00:55:25,226 --> 00:55:27,561
I'm going to try everything I want to do

591
00:55:29,033 --> 00:55:32,996
and I'm going to see people I want to see.

592
00:55:32,996 --> 00:55:39,489
Then is conducting
one of the things you want to do?

593
00:55:41,716 --> 00:55:45,119
Why don't you think about it?

594
00:55:47,751 --> 00:55:49,792
[Splendid Debut of Rising Star,
Han Eum Orchestra]

595
00:55:51,305 --> 00:55:55,038
Han Eum Orchestra Rising Star
was exactly what the name meant.

596
00:55:55,038 --> 00:55:58,330
In the melody
of Rachmaninoff Piano Concerto No.2

597
00:55:58,330 --> 00:55:59,943
with Conductor Cha Yoo Jin...

598
00:55:59,943 --> 00:56:02,145
Their performance with Pianist Son Soo Ji

599
00:56:02,145 --> 00:56:05,069
surpassed the level of college orchestra.

600
00:56:05,069 --> 00:56:08,918
The performance received
three rounds of encore and a standing ovation.

601
00:56:28,204 --> 00:56:30,330
Thank you, Chairwoman.

602
00:56:30,330 --> 00:56:33,209
I won't let you down. Thank you.

603
00:56:35,478 --> 00:56:37,947
Yes, yes, yes!

604
00:56:47,865 --> 00:56:50,901
Franz, I heard a really good news.

605
00:56:53,121 --> 00:56:55,857
The news
of the board of directors approving Rising Star

606
00:56:55,857 --> 00:56:59,994
as the official Han Eum Orchestra?

607
00:57:05,713 --> 00:57:08,570
Sunbae, you are rich.

608
00:57:08,570 --> 00:57:10,579
My uncle is.

609
00:57:10,579 --> 00:57:13,408
I've lived here the whole time,
so I feel like this is my hometown.

610
00:57:13,850 --> 00:57:17,704
This was also my grandfather's favorite house.

611
00:57:17,704 --> 00:57:20,205
You mean, you grew up here?

612
00:57:20,205 --> 00:57:21,741
Yes.

613
00:57:23,401 --> 00:57:27,005
Now I think about it,
this is the most comfortable place to me.

614
00:57:28,739 --> 00:57:30,473
It's really huge.

615
00:57:36,850 --> 00:57:40,704
What is it? Tell me, tell me, tell me...

616
00:57:40,704 --> 00:57:42,437
It's nothing.

617
00:57:42,904 --> 00:57:47,174
Rising Star was approved
as the official Han Eum Orchestra.

618
00:57:54,538 --> 00:57:58,330
- We have nothing to worry about.
- We'll get more opportunities, Il Lak.

619
00:57:58,330 --> 00:58:01,567
- We'll get recognized nationally.
- We're not losers anymore.

620
00:58:01,567 --> 00:58:06,205
I can't just sit by
and watch on such a happy day.

621
00:58:06,205 --> 00:58:08,874
- Who's going to blow the candles?
- Me! Me! Me!

622
00:58:27,590 --> 00:58:30,659
There is no way
that they'd approve it so easily.

623
00:58:32,174 --> 00:58:37,330
They could have made a big deal
out of the issues with Lee Yoon Hoo and Baby.

624
00:58:37,330 --> 00:58:39,336
But they gave up.

625
00:58:41,339 --> 00:58:43,574
What do they have in mind?

626
00:58:45,149 --> 00:58:47,746
You called me here
with an excuse of Seol Nae Il

627
00:58:47,746 --> 00:58:49,586
but the reason is Dr. Kim?

628
00:58:50,601 --> 00:58:53,871
I heard Cha Dong Woo came by
to see your concert yesterday.

629
00:58:56,163 --> 00:59:00,288
He'll flip Sun Young's heart upside down again
with your problem.

630
00:59:00,288 --> 00:59:02,302
He's been doing that all along.

631
00:59:03,038 --> 00:59:04,539
I'm sorry.

632
00:59:06,038 --> 00:59:08,538
It's been a while
since you went to Dr. Kim, right?

633
00:59:08,538 --> 00:59:11,038
Will you just waste time?

634
00:59:11,038 --> 00:59:12,413
Try as hard as you can,

635
00:59:12,413 --> 00:59:15,511
but when things don't work out,
you should learn to give up.

636
00:59:16,385 --> 00:59:19,579
If you are in the most comfortable place,
hypnotherapy works well.

637
00:59:19,579 --> 00:59:21,180
Let's give it a try.

638
00:59:26,816 --> 00:59:30,186
Raise your left arm as high as your shoulder.

639
00:59:31,256 --> 00:59:34,559
It should feel heavy
as if you're holding a dictionary.

640
00:59:36,249 --> 00:59:39,218
Your fingers are numb.

641
00:59:40,413 --> 00:59:43,416
Your pinky is getting heavy.

642
00:59:44,538 --> 00:59:46,954
You can't move it.

643
00:59:46,954 --> 00:59:50,677
Now, we're going back
to when you were 10 years old.

644
00:59:50,677 --> 00:59:54,621
Cha Yoo Jin, you're on a plane.

645
00:59:54,621 --> 00:59:56,908
We'll go to the scene now.

646
00:59:57,346 --> 00:59:59,114
What happened?

647
01:00:05,345 --> 01:00:07,146
Let's stop.

648
01:00:07,954 --> 01:00:09,996
I've tried everything, but nothing worked.

649
01:00:09,996 --> 01:00:12,392
So age regression therapy
wouldn't work either.

650
01:00:13,126 --> 01:00:14,829
We need to get to a deep hypnotic trance,

651
01:00:14,829 --> 01:00:16,996
but we can't even get to where we used to.

652
01:00:16,996 --> 01:00:19,332
Did you give up studying abroad?

653
01:00:20,200 --> 01:00:21,835
Not a chance.

654
01:00:22,188 --> 01:00:23,994
I told you before...

655
01:00:23,994 --> 01:00:26,111
about how you can easily
be susceptible to hypnosis.

656
01:00:27,641 --> 01:00:29,175
Yes.

657
01:00:29,912 --> 01:00:33,113
The one who believes
that others will support him when he falls,

658
01:00:33,113 --> 01:00:36,316
are the ones that can easily be susceptible.

659
01:00:53,236 --> 01:00:55,271
There are so many of them.

660
01:01:22,662 --> 01:01:24,864
As a music student,

661
01:01:25,406 --> 01:01:27,207
you can't just pass by this kind of place.

662
01:01:27,766 --> 01:01:30,565
I'm sorry that I came in without permission.

663
01:01:30,570 --> 01:01:31,838
It's okay.

664
01:01:35,782 --> 01:01:40,120
My father... So, Yoo Jin's grandfather...

665
01:01:41,242 --> 01:01:43,845
He really liked music.

666
01:01:54,213 --> 01:01:57,983
Gymnopedie. I like this, too.

667
01:02:07,841 --> 01:02:10,677
This was when Sunbae was little, right?

668
01:02:10,677 --> 01:02:13,246
He looks exactly the same as now.

669
01:02:15,902 --> 01:02:18,972
But I guess he wasn't afraid of water then.

670
01:02:20,153 --> 01:02:23,990
Do you know about that?

671
01:02:24,651 --> 01:02:26,186
Pardon?

672
01:02:26,626 --> 01:02:31,264
Well, this is the first time
Yoo Jin brought his girlfriend.

673
01:02:32,385 --> 01:02:35,454
I didn't know he'd really bring you here
just because I told him.

674
01:02:36,464 --> 01:02:38,264
If you're that close,
I guess you should know.

675
01:02:39,425 --> 01:02:41,126
About what?

676
01:02:43,069 --> 01:02:45,071
About Yoo Jin's accident.

677
01:02:48,281 --> 01:02:50,250
The plane accident.

678
01:02:50,837 --> 01:02:52,038
Uncle!

679
01:02:54,754 --> 01:02:56,322
What are you doing right now?
